00052 //*********************
00053 //Operand collector (OC) modelling (Syed Gilani)
00054 //*********************
00055 //The OCs are modelled similar to the GPGPU-Sim v3.x documentation and
00056 //nVIDIA patents.
00057 //the OC need the following GPGPU-Sim config options:
00058 //-gpgpu_num_reg_banks                    8 # Number of register banks (default = 8)
00059 //-gpgpu_reg_bank_use_warp_id                    0 # Use warp ID in mapping registers to banks (default = off)
00060 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_units_sp                    6 # number of collector units (default = 4)
00061 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_units_sfu                    8 # number of collector units (default = 4)
00062 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_units_mem                    2 # number of collector units (default = 2)
00063 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_units_gen                    0 # number of collector units (default = 0)
00064 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_in_ports_sp                    1 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 1)
00065 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_in_ports_sfu                    1 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 1)
00066 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_in_ports_mem                    1 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 1)
00067 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_in_ports_gen                    0 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 0)
00068 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_out_ports_sp                    1 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 1)
00069 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_out_ports_sfu                    1 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 1)
00070 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_out_ports_mem                    1 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 1)
00071 //-gpgpu_operand_collector_num_out_ports_gen                    0 # number of collector unit in ports (default = 0)
00072 
00073 //The total number of collector units and their input ports, and the number of register file banks
00074 //determine the crossbar size.

00260            * BTB branch target buffer, accessed during IF stage. Virtually indexed and virtually tagged

00263            * such as main memory (not actively fill the misses), it is passively updated under two circumstances:
00264            * 1)  when BPT@ID stage finds out current is a taken branch while BTB missed
00265            * 2)  When BPT@ID stage predicts differently than BTB
00266            * 3)  When ID stage finds out current instruction is not a branch while BTB had a hit.(mark as invalid)

00330 BranchPredictor::BranchPredictor(ParseXML* XML_interface, int ithCore_, InputParameter* interface_ip_, const CoreDynParam & dyn_p_, bool exist_)
00331 :XML(XML_interface),
00332  ithCore(ithCore_),
00333  interface_ip(*interface_ip_),
00334  coredynp(dyn_p_),
00335  globalBPT(0),
00336  localBPT(0),
00337  L1_localBPT(0),
00338  L2_localBPT(0),
00339  chooser(0),
00340  RAS(0),
00341  exist(exist_)
00342 {
00343     /*
00344      * Branch Predictor, accessed during ID stage.
00345      * McPAT's branch predictor model is the tournament branch predictor used in Alpha 21264,
00346      * including global predictor, local two level predictor, and Chooser.
00347      * The Branch predictor also includes a RAS (return address stack) for function calls
00348      * Branch predictors are tagged by thread ID and modeled as 1-way associative $
00349      * However RAS return address stacks are duplicated for each thread.
00350      * TODO:Data Width need to be computed more precisely    *
00351      */
00352     if (!exist) return;
00353     int  tag, data;
00354 
00355     clockRate = coredynp.clockRate;
00356     executionTime = coredynp.executionTime;
00357     interface_ip.assoc               = 1;
00358     interface_ip.pure_cam            = false;
00359     if (coredynp.multithreaded)
00360     {
00361 
00362         tag                              = int(log2(coredynp.num_hthreads)+ EXTRA_TAG_BITS);
00363         interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
00364         interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
00365 
00366         interface_ip.is_cache            = true;
00367         interface_ip.pure_ram            = false;
00368         }
00369     else
00370     {
00371         interface_ip.is_cache            = false;
00372         interface_ip.pure_ram            = true;
00373 
00374     }
00375     //Global predictor
00376     data                             = int(ceil(XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.global_predictor_bits/8.0));
00377     interface_ip.line_sz             = data;
00378     interface_ip.cache_sz            = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.global_predictor_entries;
00379     interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
00380     interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
00381     interface_ip.access_mode         = 2;
00382     interface_ip.throughput          = 1.0/clockRate;
00383     interface_ip.latency             = 1.0/clockRate;
00384     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
00385     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
00386     interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
00387     interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
00388     interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = 0;
00389     interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = coredynp.predictionW;
00390     interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = coredynp.predictionW;
00391     interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
00392     globalBPT = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "Global Predictor", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
00393     globalBPT->area.set_area(globalBPT->area.get_area()+ globalBPT->local_result.area);
00394     area.set_area(area.get_area()+ globalBPT->local_result.area);
00395 
00396     //Local BPT (Level 1)
00397     data                             = int(ceil(XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.local_predictor_size[0]/8.0));
00398     interface_ip.line_sz             = data;
00399     interface_ip.cache_sz            = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.local_predictor_entries;
00400     interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
00401     interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
00402     interface_ip.access_mode         = 2;
00403     interface_ip.throughput          = 1.0/clockRate;
00404     interface_ip.latency             = 1.0/clockRate;
00405     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
00406     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
00407     interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
00408     interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
00409     interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = 0;
00410     interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = coredynp.predictionW;
00411     interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = coredynp.predictionW;
00412     interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
00413     L1_localBPT = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "L1 local Predictor", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
00414     L1_localBPT->area.set_area(L1_localBPT->area.get_area()+ L1_localBPT->local_result.area);
00415     area.set_area(area.get_area()+ L1_localBPT->local_result.area);
00416 
00417     //Local BPT (Level 2)
00418     data                             = int(ceil(XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.local_predictor_size[1]/8.0));
00419     interface_ip.line_sz             = data;
00420     interface_ip.cache_sz            = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.local_predictor_entries;
00421     interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
00422     interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
00423     interface_ip.access_mode         = 2;
00424     interface_ip.throughput          = 1.0/clockRate;
00425     interface_ip.latency             = 1.0/clockRate;
00426     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
00427     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
00428     interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
00429     interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
00430     interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = 0;
00431     interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = coredynp.predictionW;
00432     interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = coredynp.predictionW;
00433     interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
00434     L2_localBPT = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "L2 local Predictor", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
00435     L2_localBPT->area.set_area(L2_localBPT->area.get_area()+ L2_localBPT->local_result.area);
00436     area.set_area(area.get_area()+ L2_localBPT->local_result.area);
00437 
00438     //Chooser
00439     data                             = int(ceil(XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.chooser_predictor_bits/8.0));
00440     interface_ip.line_sz             = data;
00441     interface_ip.cache_sz            = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].predictor.chooser_predictor_entries;
00442     interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
00443     interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
00444     interface_ip.access_mode         = 2;
00445     interface_ip.throughput          = 1.0/clockRate;
00446     interface_ip.latency             = 1.0/clockRate;
00447     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
00448     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
00449     interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
00450     interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
00451     interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = 0;
00452     interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = coredynp.predictionW;
00453     interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = coredynp.predictionW;
00454     interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
00455     chooser = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "Predictor Chooser", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
00456     chooser->area.set_area(chooser->area.get_area()+ chooser->local_result.area);
00457     area.set_area(area.get_area()+ chooser->local_result.area);
00458 
00459     //RAS return address stacks are Duplicated for each thread.
00460     interface_ip.is_cache            = false;
00461     interface_ip.pure_ram            = true;
00462     data                             = int(ceil(coredynp.pc_width/8.0));
00463     interface_ip.line_sz             = data;
00464     interface_ip.cache_sz            = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].RAS_size;
00465     interface_ip.assoc               = 1;
00466     interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
00467     interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
00468     interface_ip.access_mode         = 2;
00469     interface_ip.throughput          = 1.0/clockRate;
00470     interface_ip.latency             = 1.0/clockRate;
00471     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
00472     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
00473     interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
00474     interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
00475     interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = 0;
00476     interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = coredynp.predictionW;
00477     interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = coredynp.predictionW;
00478     interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
00479     RAS = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "RAS", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
00480     RAS->area.set_area(RAS->area.get_area()+ RAS->local_result.area*coredynp.num_hthreads);
00481     area.set_area(area.get_area()+ RAS->local_result.area*coredynp.num_hthreads);
00482 
00483 }
00484 
00485 SchedulerU::SchedulerU(ParseXML* XML_interface, int ithCore_, InputParameter* interface_ip_, const CoreDynParam & dyn_p_, bool exist_)
00486 :XML(XML_interface),
00487  ithCore(ithCore_),
00488  interface_ip(*interface_ip_),
00489  coredynp(dyn_p_),
00490  int_inst_window(0),
00491  fp_inst_window(0),
00492  ROB(0),
00493  instruction_selection(0),
00494  exist(exist_)
00495  {
00496     if (!exist) return;
00497     int   tag, data;
00498     bool  is_default=true;
00499     string tmp_name;
00500 
00501     clockRate = coredynp.clockRate;
00502     executionTime = coredynp.executionTime;
00503     if ((coredynp.core_ty==Inorder && coredynp.multithreaded))
00504     {
00505         //Instruction issue queue, in-order multi-issue or multithreaded processor also has this structure. Unified window for Inorder processors
00506         tag                              = int(log2(XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads)*coredynp.perThreadState);//This is the normal thread state bits based on Niagara Design
00507         data                             = XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_length;
00508         //NOTE: x86 inst can be very lengthy, up to 15B. Source: Intel® 64 and IA-32 Architectures
00509         //Software Developer’s Manual
00510         interface_ip.is_cache            = true;
00511         interface_ip.pure_cam            = false;
00512         interface_ip.pure_ram            = false;
00513         interface_ip.line_sz             = int(ceil(data/8.0));
00514         interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
00515         interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
00516         interface_ip.cache_sz            = XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_window_size*interface_ip.line_sz>64?XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_window_size*interface_ip.line_sz:64;
00517         interface_ip.assoc               = 0;
00518         interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
00519         interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
00520         interface_ip.access_mode         = 1;
00521         interface_ip.throughput          = 1.0/clockRate;
00522         interface_ip.latency             = 1.0/clockRate;
00523         interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
00524         interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
00525         interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
00526         interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
00527         interface_ip.num_rw_ports        = 0;
00528         interface_ip.num_rd_ports        = coredynp.peak_issueW;
00529         interface_ip.num_wr_ports        = coredynp.peak_issueW;
00530         interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports     = 0;
00531         interface_ip.num_search_ports    = coredynp.peak_issueW;
00532         int_inst_window = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "InstFetchQueue", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
00533         int_inst_window->area.set_area(int_inst_window->area.get_area()+ int_inst_window->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
00534         area.set_area(area.get_area()+ int_inst_window->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
00535         //output_data_csv(iRS.RS.local_result);
00536         Iw_height      =int_inst_window->local_result.cache_ht;
00537 
00538         /*
00539          * selection logic
00540          * In a single-issue Inorder multithreaded processor like Niagara, issue width=1*number_of_threads since the processor does need to pick up
00541          * instructions from multiple ready ones(although these ready ones are from different threads).While SMT processors do not distinguish which thread belongs to who
00542          * at the issue stage.
00543          */
00544 
00545         instruction_selection = new selection_logic(is_default, XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_window_size,
00546                 coredynp.peak_issueW*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads,
00547                 &interface_ip, Core_device, coredynp.core_ty);
00548     }
00549 
00550     if (coredynp.core_ty==OOO)
00551     {
00552         /*
00553          * CAM based instruction window
00554          * For physicalRegFilebased OOO it is the instruction issue queue, where only tags of phy regs are stored
00555          * For RS based OOO it is the Reservation station, where both tags and values of phy regs are stored
00556          * It is written once and read twice(two operands) before an instruction can be issued.
00557          * X86 instruction can be very long up to 15B. add instruction length in XML
00558          */
00559         if(coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
00560         {
00561             tag  = coredynp.phy_ireg_width;
00562             // Each time only half of the tag is compared, but two tag should be stored.
00563             // This underestimate the search power
00564             data = int((ceil((coredynp.instruction_length+2*(coredynp.phy_ireg_width - coredynp.arch_ireg_width))/2.0)/8.0));
00565             //Data width being divided by 2 means only after both operands available the whole data will be read out.
00566             //This is modeled using two equivalent readouts with half of the data width
00567             tmp_name = "InstIssueQueue";
00568         }
00569         else
00570         {
00571             tag   = coredynp.phy_ireg_width;
00572             // Each time only half of the tag is compared, but two tag should be stored.
00573             // This underestimate the search power
00574             data  = int(ceil(((coredynp.instruction_length+2*(coredynp.phy_ireg_width - coredynp.arch_ireg_width)+
00575                     2*coredynp.int_data_width)/2.0)/8.0));
00576             //Data width being divided by 2 means only after both operands available the whole data will be read out.
00577             //This is modeled using two equivalent readouts with half of the data width
00578 
00579             tmp_name = "IntReservationStation";
00580         }
00581         interface_ip.is_cache            = true;
00582         interface_ip.pure_cam            = false;
00583         interface_ip.pure_ram            = false;
00584         interface_ip.line_sz             = data;
00585         interface_ip.cache_sz            = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_window_size;
00586         interface_ip.assoc               = 0;
00587         interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
00588         interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
00589         interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
00590         interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
00591         interface_ip.access_mode         = 0;
00592         interface_ip.throughput          = 2*1.0/clockRate;
00593         interface_ip.latency             = 2*1.0/clockRate;
00594         interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
00595         interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
00596         interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
00597         interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
00598         interface_ip.num_rw_ports       = 0;
00599         interface_ip.num_rd_ports       = coredynp.peak_issueW;
00600         interface_ip.num_wr_ports       = coredynp.peak_issueW;
00601         interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports    = 0;
00602         interface_ip.num_search_ports   = coredynp.peak_issueW;
00603         int_inst_window = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, tmp_name, Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
00604         int_inst_window->area.set_area(int_inst_window->area.get_area()+ int_inst_window->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
00605         area.set_area(area.get_area()+ int_inst_window->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
00606         Iw_height      =int_inst_window->local_result.cache_ht;
00607         //FU inst window
00608         if(coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
00609         {
00610             tag  = 2*coredynp.phy_freg_width;// TODO: each time only half of the tag is compared
00611             data = int(ceil((coredynp.instruction_length+2*(coredynp.phy_freg_width - coredynp.arch_freg_width))/8.0));
00612             tmp_name = "FPIssueQueue";
00613         }
00614         else
00615         {
00616             tag   = 2*coredynp.phy_ireg_width;
00617             data  = int(ceil((coredynp.instruction_length+2*(coredynp.phy_freg_width - coredynp.arch_freg_width)+
00618                     2*coredynp.fp_data_width)/8.0));
00619             tmp_name = "FPReservationStation";
00620         }
00621         interface_ip.is_cache            = true;
00622         interface_ip.pure_cam            = false;
00623         interface_ip.pure_ram            = false;
00624         interface_ip.line_sz             = data;
00625         interface_ip.cache_sz            = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].fp_instruction_window_size;
00626         interface_ip.assoc               = 0;
00627         interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
00628         interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
00629         interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
00630         interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
00631         interface_ip.access_mode         = 0;
00632         interface_ip.throughput          = 1.0/clockRate;
00633         interface_ip.latency             = 1.0/clockRate;
00634         interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
00635         interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
00636         interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
00637         interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
00638         interface_ip.num_rw_ports       = 0;
00639         interface_ip.num_rd_ports       = coredynp.fp_issueW;
00640         interface_ip.num_wr_ports       = coredynp.fp_issueW;
00641         interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports    = 0;
00642         interface_ip.num_search_ports   = coredynp.fp_issueW;
00643         fp_inst_window = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, tmp_name, Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
00644         fp_inst_window->area.set_area(fp_inst_window->area.get_area()+ fp_inst_window->local_result.area*coredynp.num_fp_pipelines);
00645         area.set_area(area.get_area()+ fp_inst_window->local_result.area*coredynp.num_fp_pipelines);
00646         fp_Iw_height      =fp_inst_window->local_result.cache_ht;
00647 
00648         if (XML->sys.core[ithCore].ROB_size >0)
00649         {
00650             /*
00651              *  if ROB_size = 0, then the target processor does not support hardware-based
00652              *  speculation, i.e. , the processor allow OOO issue as well as OOO completion, which
00653              *  means branch must be resolved before instruction issued into instruction window, since
00654              *  there is no change to flush miss-predict branch path after instructions are issued in this situation.
00655              *
00656              *  ROB.ROB size = inflight inst. ROB is unified for int and fp inst.
00657              *  One old approach is to combine the RAT and ROB as a huge CAM structure as in AMD K7.
00658              *  However, this approach is abandoned due to its high power and poor scalablility.
00659              *  McPAT uses current implementation of ROB as circular buffer.
00660              *  ROB is written once when instruction is issued and read once when the instruction is committed.         *
00661              */
00662             int robExtra = int(ceil(5 + log2(coredynp.num_hthreads)));
00663             //5 bits are: busy, Issued, Finished, speculative, valid
00664             if(coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
00665             {
00666                 //PC is to id the instruction for recover exception.
00667                 //inst is used to map the renamed dest. registers.so that commit stage can know which reg/RRAT to update
00668 //              data = int(ceil((robExtra+coredynp.pc_width +
00669 //                      coredynp.instruction_length + 2*coredynp.phy_ireg_width)/8.0));
00670                 data = int(ceil((robExtra+coredynp.pc_width +
00671                             coredynp.phy_ireg_width)/8.0));
00672             }
00673             else
00674             {
00675                 //in RS based OOO, ROB also contains value of destination reg
00676 //              data  = int(ceil((robExtra+coredynp.pc_width +
00677 //                      coredynp.instruction_length + 2*coredynp.phy_ireg_width + coredynp.fp_data_width)/8.0));
00678                 data  = int(ceil((robExtra + coredynp.pc_width +
00679                         coredynp.phy_ireg_width + coredynp.fp_data_width)/8.0));
00680             }
00681             interface_ip.is_cache            = false;
00682             interface_ip.pure_cam            = false;
00683             interface_ip.pure_ram            = true;
00684             interface_ip.line_sz             = data;
00685             interface_ip.cache_sz            = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].ROB_size;//The XML ROB size is for all threads
00686             interface_ip.assoc               = 1;
00687             interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
00688             interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
00689             interface_ip.access_mode         = 1;
00690             interface_ip.throughput          = 1.0/clockRate;
00691             interface_ip.latency             = 1.0/clockRate;
00692             interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
00693             interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
00694             interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
00695             interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
00696             interface_ip.num_rw_ports       = 0;
00697             interface_ip.num_rd_ports       = coredynp.peak_commitW;
00698             interface_ip.num_wr_ports       = coredynp.peak_issueW;
00699             interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports    = 0;
00700             interface_ip.num_search_ports   = 0;
00701             ROB = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "ReorderBuffer", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
00702             ROB->area.set_area(ROB->area.get_area()+ ROB->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
00703             area.set_area(area.get_area()+ ROB->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
00704             ROB_height      =ROB->local_result.cache_ht;
00705         }
00706 
00707         instruction_selection = new selection_logic(is_default, XML->sys.core[ithCore].instruction_window_size,
00708                 coredynp.peak_issueW, &interface_ip, Core_device, coredynp.core_ty);
00709     }
00710 }
00711 
00712 LoadStoreU::LoadStoreU(ParseXML* XML_interface, int ithCore_, InputParameter* interface_ip_, const CoreDynParam & dyn_p_,bool exist_)
00713 :XML(XML_interface),
00714  ithCore(ithCore_),
00715  interface_ip(*interface_ip_),
00716  coredynp(dyn_p_),
00717  LSQ(0),
00718  exist(exist_)
00719 {
00720       if (!exist) return;
00721       int  idx, tag, data, size, line, assoc;
00722       bool debug= false;
00723       int ldst_opcode = XML->sys.core[ithCore].opcode_width;//16;
00724 
00725       clockRate = coredynp.clockRate;
00726       executionTime = coredynp.executionTime;
00727       cache_p = (Cache_policy)XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[7];
00728 
00729       interface_ip.num_search_ports    = XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;
00730       interface_ip.is_cache            = true;
00731       interface_ip.pure_cam            = false;
00732       interface_ip.pure_ram            = false;
00733      
00734 
00735       //Crossbar based interconnect for shared memory accesses, added by Syed
00736       //Crossbar
00737 
00738       if(XML->sys.architecture==1){
00739     xbar_shared     = new Crossbar(coredynp.num_fpus,coredynp.num_fpus,32,&(g_tp.peri_global));//Syed: coredynp.num_fpus is used as simd_width  
00740       }
00741       else{
00742       xbar_shared     = new Crossbar(coredynp.num_fpus,coredynp.num_fpus,32,&(g_tp.peri_global));//Syed: coredynp.num_fpus is used as simd_width
00743       }
00744 
00745 
00746      //TODO: Check if this line should be changed to
00747      //new Crossbar(simd_width,shared_memory_banks,word_length*simd_width,&(g_tp.peri_global));
00748 
00749     //shared memory added by Jingwen
00750       size                             = (int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[0];
00751       line                             = (int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[1];
00752       assoc                            = (int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[2];
00753       idx                              = debug?9:int(ceil(log2(size/line/assoc)));
00754       tag                              = debug?51:XML->sys.physical_address_width-idx-int(ceil(log2(line))) + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
00755       interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
00756       interface_ip.tag_w               = 1;
00757       interface_ip.cache_sz            = debug?32768:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[0];
00758       interface_ip.line_sz             = debug?64:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[1];
00759       interface_ip.assoc               = debug?8:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[2];
00760       interface_ip.nbanks              = debug?1:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[3];
00761       interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
00762       interface_ip.access_mode         = 0;//debug?0:XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[5];
00763       interface_ip.throughput          = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[4]/clockRate;
00764       interface_ip.latency             = debug?3.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].sharedmemory.dcache_config[5]/clockRate;
00765       interface_ip.is_cache          = true;
00766       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
00767       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
00768       interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
00769       interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
00770       interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;//usually In-order has 1 and OOO has 2 at least.
00771       interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 0;
00772       interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = 0;
00773       interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
00774       sharedmemory.caches = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "sharedmemory", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
00775       sharedmemory.area.set_area(sharedmemory.area.get_area()+ sharedmemory.caches->local_result.area);

01111       tcache.ifb = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "tcacheFillBuffer", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01112       tcache.area.set_area(tcache.area.get_area()+ tcache.ifb->local_result.area);
01113       area.set_area(area.get_area()+ tcache.ifb->local_result.area);
01114       //output_data_csv(tcache.ifb.local_result);
01115 
01116       //prefetch buffer
01117       tag                              = XML->sys.physical_address_width + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;//check with previous entries to decide wthether to merge.
01118       data                             = tcache.caches->l_ip.line_sz;//separate queue to prevent from cache polution.
01119       interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
01120       interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
01121       interface_ip.line_sz             = data;//int(pow(2.0,ceil(log2(data))));
01122       interface_ip.cache_sz            = XML->sys.core[ithCore].tcache.buffer_sizes[2]*interface_ip.line_sz;
01123       interface_ip.assoc               = 0;
01124       interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01125       interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
01126       interface_ip.access_mode         = 2;
01127       interface_ip.throughput          = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].tcache.dcache_config[4]/clockRate;
01128       interface_ip.latency             = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].tcache.dcache_config[5]/clockRate;
01129       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01130       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01131       interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
01132       interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
01133       interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;;
01134       interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 0;
01135       interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = 0;
01136       interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
01137       tcache.prefetchb = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "tcacheprefetchBuffer", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01138       tcache.area.set_area(tcache.area.get_area()+ tcache.prefetchb->local_result.area);
01139       area.set_area(area.get_area()+ tcache.prefetchb->local_result.area);
01140       //output_data_csv(tcache.prefetchb.local_result);
01141 
01142       //WBB
01143       if (cache_p==Write_back)
01144       {
01145           tag                              = XML->sys.physical_address_width + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
01146           data                             = tcache.caches->l_ip.line_sz;
01147           interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
01148           interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
01149           interface_ip.line_sz             = data;
01150           interface_ip.cache_sz            = XML->sys.core[ithCore].tcache.buffer_sizes[3]*interface_ip.line_sz;
01151           interface_ip.assoc               = 0;
01152           interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01153           interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
01154           interface_ip.access_mode         = 2;
01155           interface_ip.throughput          = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].tcache.dcache_config[4]/clockRate;
01156           interface_ip.latency             = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].tcache.dcache_config[5]/clockRate;
01157           interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01158           interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01159           interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
01160           interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
01161           interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;
01162           interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 0;
01163           interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = 0;
01164           interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
01165           tcache.wbb = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "tcacheWBB", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01166           tcache.area.set_area(tcache.area.get_area()+ tcache.wbb->local_result.area);
01167           area.set_area(area.get_area()+ tcache.wbb->local_result.area);
01168           //output_data_csv(tcache.wbb.local_result);
01169       }
01170 
01171 
01172 
01173 
01174    /*
01175     * dcache starts here
01176     */   
01177     //Dcache
01178       size                             = (int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[0];
01179       line                             = (int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[1];
01180       assoc                            = (int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[2];
01181       idx                              = debug?9:int(ceil(log2(size/line/assoc)));
01182       tag                              = debug?51:XML->sys.physical_address_width-idx-int(ceil(log2(line))) + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
01183       interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
01184       interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
01185       interface_ip.cache_sz            = debug?32768:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[0];
01186       interface_ip.line_sz             = debug?64:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[1];
01187       interface_ip.assoc               = debug?8:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[2];
01188       interface_ip.nbanks              = debug?1:(int)XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[3];
01189       interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
01190       interface_ip.access_mode         = 0;//debug?0:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[5];
01191       interface_ip.throughput          = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[4]/clockRate;
01192       interface_ip.latency             = debug?3.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[5]/clockRate;
01193       interface_ip.is_cache          = true;
01194       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01195       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01196       interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
01197       interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
01198       interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;//usually In-order has 1 and OOO has 2 at least.
01199       interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 0;
01200       interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = 0;
01201       interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
01202       dcache.caches = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "dcache", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01203       dcache.area.set_area(dcache.area.get_area()+ dcache.caches->local_result.area);
01204       area.set_area(area.get_area()+ dcache.caches->local_result.area);
01205       //output_data_csv(dcache.caches.local_result);
01206 
01207 
01208       //dCache controllers
01209       //miss buffer
01210       tag                              = XML->sys.physical_address_width + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
01211       data                             = (XML->sys.physical_address_width) + int(ceil(log2(size/line))) + dcache.caches->l_ip.line_sz*8;
01212       interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
01213       interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
01214       interface_ip.line_sz             = int(ceil(data/8.0));//int(ceil(pow(2.0,ceil(log2(data)))/8.0));
01215       interface_ip.cache_sz            = XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.buffer_sizes[0]*interface_ip.line_sz;
01216       interface_ip.assoc               = 0;
01217       interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01218       interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
01219       interface_ip.access_mode         = 2;
01220       interface_ip.throughput          = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[4]/clockRate;
01221       interface_ip.latency             = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[5]/clockRate;
01222       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01223       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01224       interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
01225       interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
01226       interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;;
01227       interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 0;
01228       interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = 0;
01229       interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
01230       dcache.missb = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "dcacheMissBuffer", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01231       dcache.area.set_area(dcache.area.get_area()+ dcache.missb->local_result.area);
01232       area.set_area(area.get_area()+ dcache.missb->local_result.area);
01233       //output_data_csv(dcache.missb.local_result);
01234 
01235       //fill buffer
01236       tag                              = XML->sys.physical_address_width + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
01237       data                             = dcache.caches->l_ip.line_sz;
01238       interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
01239       interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
01240       interface_ip.line_sz             = data;//int(pow(2.0,ceil(log2(data))));
01241       interface_ip.cache_sz            = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.buffer_sizes[1];
01242       interface_ip.assoc               = 0;
01243       interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01244       interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
01245       interface_ip.access_mode         = 2;
01246       interface_ip.throughput          = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[4]/clockRate;
01247       interface_ip.latency             = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[5]/clockRate;
01248       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01249       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01250       interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
01251       interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
01252       interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;;
01253       interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 0;
01254       interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = 0;
01255       interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
01256       dcache.ifb = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "dcacheFillBuffer", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01257       dcache.area.set_area(dcache.area.get_area()+ dcache.ifb->local_result.area);
01258       area.set_area(area.get_area()+ dcache.ifb->local_result.area);
01259       //output_data_csv(dcache.ifb.local_result);
01260 
01261       //prefetch buffer
01262       tag                              = XML->sys.physical_address_width + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;//check with previous entries to decide wthether to merge.
01263       data                             = dcache.caches->l_ip.line_sz;//separate queue to prevent from cache polution.
01264       interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
01265       interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
01266       interface_ip.line_sz             = data;//int(pow(2.0,ceil(log2(data))));
01267       interface_ip.cache_sz            = XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.buffer_sizes[2]*interface_ip.line_sz;
01268       interface_ip.assoc               = 0;
01269       interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01270       interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
01271       interface_ip.access_mode         = 2;
01272       interface_ip.throughput          = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[4]/clockRate;
01273       interface_ip.latency             = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[5]/clockRate;
01274       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01275       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01276       interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
01277       interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
01278       interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;;
01279       interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 0;
01280       interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = 0;
01281       interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
01282       dcache.prefetchb = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "dcacheprefetchBuffer", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01283       dcache.area.set_area(dcache.area.get_area()+ dcache.prefetchb->local_result.area);
01284       area.set_area(area.get_area()+ dcache.prefetchb->local_result.area);
01285       //output_data_csv(dcache.prefetchb.local_result);
01286 
01287       //WBB
01288       if (cache_p==Write_back)
01289       {
01290           tag                              = XML->sys.physical_address_width + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
01291           data                             = dcache.caches->l_ip.line_sz;
01292           interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
01293           interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
01294           interface_ip.line_sz             = data;
01295           interface_ip.cache_sz            = XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.buffer_sizes[3]*interface_ip.line_sz;
01296           interface_ip.assoc               = 0;
01297           interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01298           interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
01299           interface_ip.access_mode         = 2;
01300           interface_ip.throughput          = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[4]/clockRate;
01301           interface_ip.latency             = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[5]/clockRate;
01302           interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01303           interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01304           interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
01305           interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
01306           interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;
01307           interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 0;
01308           interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = 0;
01309           interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
01310           dcache.wbb = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "dcacheWBB", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01311           dcache.area.set_area(dcache.area.get_area()+ dcache.wbb->local_result.area);
01312           area.set_area(area.get_area()+ dcache.wbb->local_result.area);
01313           //output_data_csv(dcache.wbb.local_result);
01314       }
01315 
01316       /*
01317        * LSU--in-order processors do not have separate load queue: unified lsq
01318        * partitioned among threads
01319        * it is actually the store queue but for inorder processors it serves as both loadQ and StoreQ
01320        */
01321       tag                              = ldst_opcode+XML->sys.virtual_address_width +int(ceil(log2(XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads))) + EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
01322       data                             = XML->sys.machine_bits;
01323       interface_ip.is_cache            = true;
01324       interface_ip.line_sz             = int(ceil(data/32.0))*4;
01325       interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
01326       interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
01327       interface_ip.cache_sz            = XML->sys.core[ithCore].store_buffer_size*interface_ip.line_sz*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads;
01328       interface_ip.assoc               = 0;
01329       interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01330       interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
01331       interface_ip.access_mode         = 1;
01332       interface_ip.throughput          = 1.0/clockRate;
01333       interface_ip.latency             = 1.0/clockRate;
01334       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01335       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01336       interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
01337       interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
01338       interface_ip.num_rw_ports        = 0;
01339       interface_ip.num_rd_ports        = XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;
01340       interface_ip.num_wr_ports        = XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;
01341       interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports     = 0;
01342       interface_ip.num_search_ports    =XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;
01343       LSQ = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "Load(Store)Queue", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01344       LSQ->area.set_area(LSQ->area.get_area()+ LSQ->local_result.area);
01345       area.set_area(area.get_area()+ LSQ->local_result.area);
01346       area.set_area(area.get_area()*cdb_overhead);
01347       //output_data_csv(LSQ.LSQ.local_result);
01348       lsq_height=LSQ->local_result.cache_ht*sqrt(cdb_overhead);/*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads*/
01349 
01350       if ((coredynp.core_ty==OOO) && (XML->sys.core[ithCore].load_buffer_size >0))
01351       {
01352           interface_ip.line_sz             = int(ceil(data/32.0))*4;
01353           interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
01354           interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
01355           interface_ip.cache_sz            = XML->sys.core[ithCore].load_buffer_size*interface_ip.line_sz*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads;
01356           interface_ip.assoc               = 0;
01357           interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01358           interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
01359           interface_ip.access_mode         = 1;
01360           interface_ip.throughput          = 1.0/clockRate;
01361           interface_ip.latency             = 1.0/clockRate;
01362           interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01363           interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01364           interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
01365           interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
01366           interface_ip.num_rw_ports        = 0;
01367           interface_ip.num_rd_ports        = XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;
01368           interface_ip.num_wr_ports        = XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;
01369           interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports     = 0;
01370           interface_ip.num_search_ports    =XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;
01371           LoadQ = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "LoadQueue", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01372           LoadQ->area.set_area(LoadQ->area.get_area()+ LoadQ->local_result.area);
01373           area.set_area(area.get_area()+ LoadQ->local_result.area);
01374           area.set_area(area.get_area()*cdb_overhead);
01375           //output_data_csv(LoadQ.LoadQ.local_result);
01376           lsq_height=(LSQ->local_result.cache_ht + LoadQ->local_result.cache_ht)*sqrt(cdb_overhead);/*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads*/
01377       }
01378 
01379 }
01380 
01381 MemManU::MemManU(ParseXML* XML_interface, int ithCore_, InputParameter* interface_ip_, const CoreDynParam & dyn_p_,bool exist_)
01382 :XML(XML_interface),
01383  ithCore(ithCore_),
01384  interface_ip(*interface_ip_),
01385  coredynp(dyn_p_),
01386  itlb(0),
01387  dtlb(0),
01388  exist(exist_)
01389 {
01390       if (!exist) return;
01391       int  tag, data;
01392       bool debug= false;
01393 
01394       clockRate = coredynp.clockRate;
01395       executionTime = coredynp.executionTime;
01396 
01397       interface_ip.is_cache            = true;
01398       interface_ip.pure_cam            = false;
01399       interface_ip.pure_ram            = false;
01400       interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
01401       //Itlb TLBs are partioned among threads according to Nigara and Nehalem
01402       tag                              = XML->sys.virtual_address_width- int(floor(log2(XML->sys.virtual_memory_page_size))) + int(ceil(log2(XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads)))+ EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
01403       data                             = XML->sys.physical_address_width- int(floor(log2(XML->sys.virtual_memory_page_size)));
01404       interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
01405       interface_ip.line_sz             = int(ceil(data/8.0));//int(ceil(pow(2.0,ceil(log2(data)))/8.0));
01406       interface_ip.cache_sz            = XML->sys.core[ithCore].itlb.number_entries*interface_ip.line_sz;//*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads;
01407       interface_ip.assoc               = 0;
01408       interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01409       interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
01410       interface_ip.access_mode         = 0;
01411       interface_ip.throughput          = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[4]/clockRate;
01412       interface_ip.latency             = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].icache.icache_config[5]/clockRate;
01413       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01414       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01415       interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
01416       interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
01417       interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = 0;
01418       interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 0;
01419       interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_instruction_fetch_ports;
01420       interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
01421       interface_ip.num_search_ports    = debug?1:XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_instruction_fetch_ports;
01422       itlb = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "ITLB", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01423       itlb->area.set_area(itlb->area.get_area()+ itlb->local_result.area);
01424       area.set_area(area.get_area()+ itlb->local_result.area);
01425       //output_data_csv(itlb.tlb.local_result);
01426 
01427       //dtlb
01428       tag                              = XML->sys.virtual_address_width- int(floor(log2(XML->sys.virtual_memory_page_size))) +int(ceil(log2(XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads)))+ EXTRA_TAG_BITS;
01429       data                             = XML->sys.physical_address_width- int(floor(log2(XML->sys.virtual_memory_page_size)));
01430       interface_ip.specific_tag        = 1;
01431       interface_ip.tag_w               = tag;
01432       interface_ip.line_sz             = int(ceil(data/8.0));//int(ceil(pow(2.0,ceil(log2(data)))/8.0));
01433       interface_ip.cache_sz            = XML->sys.core[ithCore].dtlb.number_entries*interface_ip.line_sz;//*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads;
01434       interface_ip.assoc               = 0;
01435       interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01436       interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
01437       interface_ip.access_mode         = 0;
01438       interface_ip.throughput          = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[4]/clockRate;
01439       interface_ip.latency             = debug?1.0/clockRate:XML->sys.core[ithCore].dcache.dcache_config[5]/clockRate;
01440       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01441       interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01442       interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
01443       interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
01444       interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = 0;
01445       interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 0;
01446       interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;
01447       interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
01448       interface_ip.num_search_ports = XML->sys.core[ithCore].memory_ports;
01449       dtlb = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "DTLB", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01450       dtlb->area.set_area(dtlb->area.get_area()+ dtlb->local_result.area);
01451       area.set_area(area.get_area()+ dtlb->local_result.area);
01452       //output_data_csv(dtlb.tlb.local_result);

01457 RegFU::RegFU(ParseXML* XML_interface, int ithCore_, InputParameter* interface_ip_, const CoreDynParam & dyn_p_,double exClockRate,bool exist_)
01458 :XML(XML_interface),
01459  ithCore(ithCore_),
01460  interface_ip(*interface_ip_),
01461  coredynp(dyn_p_),
01462  IRF (0),
01463  FRF (0),
01464  RFWIN (0),
01465  exist(exist_)
01466  {
01467     /*
01468      * processors have separate architectural register files for each thread.
01469      * therefore, the bypass buses need to travel across all the register files.
01470      */
01471     if (!exist) return;
01472     int  data;
01473     clockRate = exClockRate;//coredynp.clockRate;
01474     executionTime = coredynp.executionTime;
01475   /*********************************************************************************
01476     * OC stage modelling (Syed Gilani)
01477     *********************************************************************************/
01478   
01479   //Crossbar
01480  
01481     if(XML->sys.architecture==1){
01482   xbar_rfu     = new Crossbar(XML->sys.core[ithCore].rf_banks/2,XML->sys.core[ithCore].collector_units/2
01483                          ,(128),&(g_tp.peri_global));
01484     }else{
01485   xbar_rfu     = new Crossbar(XML->sys.core[ithCore].rf_banks,XML->sys.core[ithCore].collector_units
01486                          ,(128),&(g_tp.peri_global));
01487     }
01488 
01489   //new Crossbar(simd_width,shared_memory_banks,word_length*simd_width,&(g_tp.peri_global));
01490 
01491   //Arbiter
01492   arbiter_rfu = new MCPAT_Arbiter(XML->sys.core[ithCore].rf_banks,XML->sys.core[ithCore].collector_units , 1,&(g_tp.peri_global));
01493 
01494 
01495 
01496     // RF banks modelled here for GPGPU-Sim (Syed Gilani)
01497     //
01498     //**********************************IRF***************************************
01499     data                             = coredynp.int_data_width;
01500   //data               *= 8;
01501     interface_ip.is_cache            = false;
01502     interface_ip.pure_cam            = false;
01503     interface_ip.pure_ram            = true;
01504 
01505     interface_ip.line_sz             = 16;//int(ceil(data/32.0))*4 * XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/4 ;//2 for Tesla as RF width half of SIMD width
01506 
01507     interface_ip.line_sz             = 16;//int(ceil(data/32.0))*4 * XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/2 ;//2 for Tesla as RF width half of SIMD width
01508 
01509     interface_ip.cache_sz            = coredynp.num_IRF_entry*4;
01510     interface_ip.assoc               = 1;
01511     interface_ip.nbanks              = XML->sys.core[ithCore].rf_banks;
01512 
01513     interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;//interface_ip.line_sz*XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/4; //2 for Tesla and 4 for Fermi
01514 
01515     interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;//interface_ip.line_sz*XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/2; //2 for Tesla and 4 for Fermi
01516 
01517 
01518     interface_ip.access_mode         = 1;
01519     interface_ip.throughput          = 1/(clockRate);
01520     interface_ip.latency             = 8.0/(clockRate);
01521     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01522     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01523     interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 1;
01524     interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 0;
01525     interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = 0;//this is the transfer port for saving/restoring states when exceptions happen.
01526     interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 1;//2*coredynp.peak_issueW;
01527     interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = 1;//coredynp.peak_issueW;
01528     interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
01529     IRF = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "Integer Register File", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01530 
01531     IRF->area.set_area(IRF->area.get_area()+ IRF->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines*cdb_overhead);
01532 
01533 
01534     area.set_area(area.get_area()+ IRF->local_result.area
01535          + xbar_rfu->area.get_area() + arbiter_rfu->area.get_area());
01536     if(XML->sys.architecture==1){
01537     IRF->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic *= .33;
01538     IRF->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic *= .33;
01539     }
01540     else {
01541     IRF->local_result.power.readOp.dynamic *= .55;
01542     IRF->local_result.power.writeOp.dynamic *= .55;
01543     }
01544 
01545 
01546 
01547 
01551     data                             = 32;
01552   //data               *= 8;
01553     interface_ip.is_cache            = false;
01554     interface_ip.pure_cam            = false;
01555     interface_ip.pure_ram            = true;
01556 
01557     interface_ip.line_sz             = 4;//int(ceil(data/32.0))*4 * XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/4 ;//2 for Tesla as RF width half of SIMD width
01558 
01559     interface_ip.line_sz             = 4;//int(ceil(data/32.0))*4 * XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/2 ;//2 for Tesla as RF width half of SIMD width
01560 
01561     interface_ip.cache_sz            = 8*4;
01562     interface_ip.assoc               = 1;
01563     interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01564 
01565     interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz;//interface_ip.line_sz*XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/4; //2 for Tesla and 4 for Fermi
01566 
01567     interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz;//interface_ip.line_sz*XML->sys.core[ithCore].simd_width/2; //2 for Tesla and 4 for Fermi
01568 
01569 
01570     interface_ip.access_mode         = 1;
01571     interface_ip.throughput          = 1.0/(clockRate);
01572     interface_ip.latency             = 1.0/(clockRate);
01573     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01574     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01575     interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 1;
01576     interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 0;
01577     interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = 0;//this is the transfer port for saving/restoring states when exceptions happen.
01578     interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 1;//2*coredynp.peak_issueW;
01579     interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = 1;//coredynp.peak_issueW;
01580     interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
01581     OPC = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "Operand collectors", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01582 
01583     OPC->area.set_area(OPC->area.get_area()+ OPC->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines*cdb_overhead);
01584 
01585 
01586     area.set_area(area.get_area()+ OPC->local_result.area);
01587 
01588 
01589 
01590 
01591     /********
01592      * For GPGPUSim (Syed Gilani)
01593      * Do not include FRF in final results for GPU. Only model the IRF
01594      ********/
01595 
01596     //**********************************FRF***************************************
01597     data                             = coredynp.fp_data_width;
01598   //data               *= 8;
01599     interface_ip.is_cache            = false;
01600     interface_ip.pure_cam            = false;
01601     interface_ip.pure_ram            = true;
01602     interface_ip.line_sz             = int(ceil(data/32.0))*4;
01603     interface_ip.cache_sz            = coredynp.num_FRF_entry*interface_ip.line_sz;
01604     interface_ip.assoc               = 1;
01605     interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01606     interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
01607     interface_ip.access_mode         = 1;
01608     interface_ip.throughput          = 1.0/clockRate;
01609     interface_ip.latency             = 1.0/clockRate;
01610     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01611     interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01612     interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
01613     interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
01614     interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = 1;//this is the transfer port for saving/restoring states when exceptions happen.
01615     interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 2*XML->sys.core[ithCore].issue_width;
01616     //interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 1;
01617     interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = XML->sys.core[ithCore].issue_width;
01618     //interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = 1;
01619     interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
01620     FRF = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "Floating point Register File", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01621     //FRF->area.set_area(FRF->area.get_area()+ FRF->local_result.area*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads*coredynp.num_fp_pipelines*cdb_overhead);
01622     //area.set_area(area.get_area()+ FRF->local_result.area*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads*coredynp.num_fp_pipelines*cdb_overhead);
01623     //area.set_area(area.get_area()*cdb_overhead);
01624     //output_data_csv(FRF.RF.local_result);
01625     int_regfile_height= IRF->local_result.cache_ht*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads*sqrt(cdb_overhead);
01626     fp_regfile_height=0;
01627     //fp_regfile_height = FRF->local_result.cache_ht*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads*sqrt(cdb_overhead);
01628     //since a EXU is associated with each pipeline, the cdb should not have longer length.
01629     if (coredynp.regWindowing)
01630     {
01631         //*********************************REG_WIN************************************
01632         data                             = coredynp.int_data_width; //ECC, and usually 2 regs are transfered together during window shifting.Niagara Mega cell
01633         interface_ip.is_cache            = false;
01634         interface_ip.pure_cam            = false;
01635         interface_ip.pure_ram            = true;
01636         interface_ip.line_sz             = int(ceil(data/8.0));
01637         interface_ip.cache_sz            = XML->sys.core[ithCore].register_windows_size*IRF->l_ip.cache_sz*XML->sys.core[ithCore].number_hardware_threads;
01638         interface_ip.assoc               = 1;
01639         interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01640         interface_ip.out_w               = interface_ip.line_sz*8;
01641         interface_ip.access_mode         = 1;
01642         interface_ip.throughput          = 4.0/clockRate;
01643         interface_ip.latency             = 4.0/clockRate;
01644         interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01645         interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;
01646         interface_ip.obj_func_leak_power = 0;
01647         interface_ip.obj_func_cycle_t    = 1;
01648         interface_ip.num_rw_ports    = 1;//this is the transfer port for saving/restoring states when exceptions happen.
01649         interface_ip.num_rd_ports    = 0;
01650         interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = 0;
01651         interface_ip.num_se_rd_ports = 0;
01652         RFWIN = new ArrayST(&interface_ip, "RegWindow", Core_device, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01653         RFWIN->area.set_area(RFWIN->area.get_area()+ RFWIN->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
01654         area.set_area(area.get_area()+ RFWIN->local_result.area*coredynp.num_pipelines);
01655         //output_data_csv(RFWIN.RF.local_result);
01656     }
01657 
01658 
01659  }
01660 
01661 EXECU::EXECU(ParseXML* XML_interface, int ithCore_, InputParameter* interface_ip_, double lsq_height_, const CoreDynParam & dyn_p_,  double exClockRate, bool exist_)
01662 :XML(XML_interface),
01663  ithCore(ithCore_),
01664  interface_ip(*interface_ip_),
01665  lsq_height(lsq_height_),
01666  coredynp(dyn_p_),
01667  rfu(0),
01668  scheu(0),
01669  fp_u(0),
01670  exeu(0),
01671  mul(0),
01672  int_bypass(0),
01673  intTagBypass(0),
01674  int_mul_bypass(0),
01675  intTag_mul_Bypass(0),
01676  fp_bypass(0),
01677  fpTagBypass(0),
01678  exist(exist_),
01679  rf_fu_clockRate(exClockRate)
01680 {
01681       if (!exist) return;
01682       double fu_height = 0.0;
01683       clockRate = coredynp.clockRate;
01684         //cout <<"EXECU exClockRate: "<<exClockRate<<endl;
01685       executionTime = coredynp.executionTime;
01686       rfu   = new RegFU(XML, ithCore, &interface_ip,coredynp,exClockRate);
01687       scheu = new SchedulerU(XML, ithCore, &interface_ip,coredynp);
01688       exeu  = new FunctionalUnit(XML, ithCore,&interface_ip, coredynp, ALU,exClockRate);
01689       area.set_area(area.get_area()+ exeu->area.get_area() + rfu->area.get_area() +scheu->area.get_area() );
01690       fu_height = exeu->FU_height;
01691       if (coredynp.num_fpus >0)
01692       {
01693           fp_u  = new FunctionalUnit(XML, ithCore,&interface_ip, coredynp, FPU, exClockRate);
01694           area.set_area(area.get_area()+ fp_u->area.get_area());
01695       }
01696       if (coredynp.num_muls >0)
01697       {
01698           mul   = new FunctionalUnit(XML, ithCore,&interface_ip, coredynp, MUL, exClockRate);
01699           area.set_area(area.get_area()+ mul->area.get_area());
01700           fu_height +=  mul->FU_height;
01701       }
01702       /*
01703        * broadcast logic, including int-broadcast; int_tag-broadcast; fp-broadcast; fp_tag-broadcast
01704        * integer by pass has two paths and fp has 3 paths.
01705        * on the same bus there are multiple tri-state drivers and muxes that go to different components on the same bus
01706        */
01707       if (XML->sys.Embedded)
01708             {
01709             interface_ip.wt                  =Global_30;
01710             interface_ip.wire_is_mat_type = 0;
01711             interface_ip.wire_os_mat_type = 0;
01712             interface_ip.throughput       = 1.0/clockRate;
01713             interface_ip.latency          = 1.0/clockRate;
01714             }
01715         else
01716             {
01717             interface_ip.wt                  =Global;
01718             interface_ip.wire_is_mat_type = 2;//start from semi-global since local wires are already used
01719             interface_ip.wire_os_mat_type = 2;
01720             interface_ip.throughput       = 10.0/clockRate; //Do not care
01721             interface_ip.latency          = 10.0/clockRate;
01722             }
01723 
01724       if (coredynp.core_ty==Inorder)
01725       {//
01726           int_bypass   = new interconnect("Int Bypass Data", Core_device, 1, 1, int(ceil(XML->sys.machine_bits/32.0)*32),
01727                   rfu->int_regfile_height + exeu->FU_height + lsq_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01728                   false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01729           bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area() + int_bypass->area.get_area());
01730           intTagBypass = new interconnect("Int Bypass tag" , Core_device, 1, 1, coredynp.perThreadState,
01731                   rfu->int_regfile_height + exeu->FU_height + lsq_height + scheu->Iw_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01732                   false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01733           bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area()  +intTagBypass->area.get_area());
01734 
01735           if (coredynp.num_muls>0)
01736           {
01737               int_mul_bypass     = new interconnect("Mul Bypass Data" , Core_device, 1, 1, int(ceil(XML->sys.machine_bits/32.0)*32*1.5),
01738                       rfu->fp_regfile_height + exeu->FU_height + mul->FU_height + lsq_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01739                       false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01740               bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area()  +int_mul_bypass->area.get_area());
01741               intTag_mul_Bypass  = new interconnect("Mul Bypass tag"  , Core_device, 1, 1, coredynp.perThreadState,
01742                       rfu->fp_regfile_height + exeu->FU_height + mul->FU_height + lsq_height + scheu->Iw_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01743                       false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01744               bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area()  +intTag_mul_Bypass->area.get_area());
01745           }
01746 
01747           /*
01748           if (coredynp.num_fpus>0)
01749           {
01750               fp_bypass    = new interconnect("FP Bypass Data" , Core_device, 1, 1, int(ceil(XML->sys.machine_bits/32.0)*32*1.5),
01751                       rfu->fp_regfile_height + fp_u->FU_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01752                       false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01753               bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area()  +fp_bypass->area.get_area());
01754               fpTagBypass  = new interconnect("FP Bypass tag"  , Core_device, 1, 1, coredynp.perThreadState,
01755                       rfu->fp_regfile_height + fp_u->FU_height + lsq_height + scheu->Iw_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01756                       false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01757               bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area()  +fpTagBypass->area.get_area());
01758           }*/
01759       } /* if (coredynp.core_ty==Inorder) */ 
01760       else
01761       {//OOO
01762           if (coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
01763           {
01764               /* For physical register based OOO,
01765                * data broadcast interconnects cover across functional units, lsq, inst windows and register files,
01766                * while tag broadcast interconnects also cover across ROB
01767                */
01768               int_bypass   = new interconnect("Int Bypass Data", Core_device, 1, 1, int(ceil(coredynp.int_data_width)),
01769                                 rfu->int_regfile_height + exeu->FU_height + lsq_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01770                                 false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01771               bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area()  +int_bypass->area.get_area());
01772               intTagBypass = new interconnect("Int Bypass tag" , Core_device, 1, 1, coredynp.phy_ireg_width,
01773                                 rfu->int_regfile_height + exeu->FU_height + lsq_height + scheu->Iw_height + scheu->ROB_height , &interface_ip, 3,
01774                                 false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01775 
01776               if (coredynp.num_muls>0)
01777               {
01778                   int_mul_bypass   = new interconnect("Mul Bypass Data", Core_device, 1, 1, int(ceil(coredynp.int_data_width)),
01779                                         rfu->int_regfile_height + exeu->FU_height + mul->FU_height + lsq_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01780                                         false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01781                   intTag_mul_Bypass = new interconnect("Mul Bypass tag" , Core_device, 1, 1, coredynp.phy_ireg_width,
01782                                         rfu->int_regfile_height + exeu->FU_height + mul->FU_height + lsq_height + scheu->Iw_height + scheu->ROB_height , &interface_ip, 3,
01783                                         false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01784                   bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area()  +int_mul_bypass->area.get_area());
01785                   bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area()  +intTag_mul_Bypass->area.get_area());
01786               }
01787 
01788               if (coredynp.num_fpus>0)
01789               {
01790                   fp_bypass    = new interconnect("FP Bypass Data" , Core_device, 1, 1, int(ceil(coredynp.fp_data_width)),
01791                                   rfu->fp_regfile_height + fp_u->FU_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01792                                   false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01793                   fpTagBypass  = new interconnect("FP Bypass tag"  , Core_device, 1, 1, coredynp.phy_freg_width,
01794                                   rfu->fp_regfile_height + fp_u->FU_height + lsq_height + scheu->fp_Iw_height + scheu->ROB_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01795                                   false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01796                   bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area()  +fp_bypass->area.get_area());
01797                   bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area()  +fpTagBypass->area.get_area());
01798               }
01799           }
01800           else
01801           {
01802              /*
01803               * In RS based processor both data and tag are broadcast together,
01804               * covering functional units, lsq, nst windows, register files, and ROBs
01805               */
01806               int_bypass   = new interconnect("Int Bypass Data", Core_device, 1, 1, int(ceil(coredynp.int_data_width)),
01807                                 rfu->int_regfile_height + exeu->FU_height + lsq_height + scheu->Iw_height + scheu->ROB_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01808                                   false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01809               intTagBypass = new interconnect("Int Bypass tag" , Core_device, 1, 1, coredynp.phy_ireg_width,
01810                                 rfu->int_regfile_height + exeu->FU_height + lsq_height + scheu->Iw_height + scheu->ROB_height , &interface_ip, 3,
01811                                   false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01812               bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area() +int_bypass->area.get_area());
01813               bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area() +intTagBypass->area.get_area());
01814               if (coredynp.num_muls>0)
01815               {
01816                   int_mul_bypass   = new interconnect("Mul Bypass Data", Core_device, 1, 1, int(ceil(coredynp.int_data_width)),
01817                                     rfu->int_regfile_height + exeu->FU_height + mul->FU_height + lsq_height + scheu->Iw_height + scheu->ROB_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01818                                       false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01819                   intTag_mul_Bypass = new interconnect("Mul Bypass tag" , Core_device, 1, 1, coredynp.phy_ireg_width,
01820                                     rfu->int_regfile_height + exeu->FU_height + mul->FU_height + lsq_height + scheu->Iw_height + scheu->ROB_height , &interface_ip, 3,
01821                                       false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01822                   bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area() +int_mul_bypass->area.get_area());
01823                   bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area() +intTag_mul_Bypass->area.get_area());
01824               }
01825 
01826               if (coredynp.num_fpus>0)
01827               {
01828                   fp_bypass    = new interconnect("FP Bypass Data" , Core_device, 1, 1, int(ceil(coredynp.fp_data_width)),
01829                           rfu->fp_regfile_height + fp_u->FU_height + lsq_height + scheu->fp_Iw_height + scheu->ROB_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01830                           false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01831                   fpTagBypass  = new interconnect("FP Bypass tag"  , Core_device, 1, 1, coredynp.phy_freg_width,
01832                           rfu->fp_regfile_height + fp_u->FU_height + lsq_height + scheu->fp_Iw_height + scheu->ROB_height, &interface_ip, 3,
01833                           false, 1.0, coredynp.opt_local, coredynp.core_ty);
01834                   bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area() +fp_bypass->area.get_area());
01835                   bypass.area.set_area(bypass.area.get_area() +fpTagBypass->area.get_area());
01836               }
01837           } /* else */

01843 
01844 RENAMINGU::RENAMINGU(ParseXML* XML_interface, int ithCore_, InputParameter* interface_ip_, const CoreDynParam & dyn_p_,bool exist_)
01845 :XML(XML_interface),
01846  ithCore(ithCore_),
01847  interface_ip(*interface_ip_),
01848  coredynp(dyn_p_),
01849  iFRAT(0),
01850  fFRAT(0),
01851  iRRAT(0),
01852  fRRAT(0),
01853  ifreeL(0),
01854  ffreeL(0),
01855  idcl(0),
01856  fdcl(0),
01857  RAHT(0),
01858  exist(exist_)
01859  {
01860     /*
01861      * Although renaming logic maybe be used in in-order processors,
01862      * McPAT assumes no renaming logic is used since the performance gain is very limited and
01863      * the only major inorder processor with renaming logic is Itainium
01864      * that is a VLIW processor and different from current McPAT's model.
01865      * physical register base OOO must have Dual-RAT architecture or equivalent structure.FRAT:FrontRAT, RRAT:RetireRAT;
01866      * i,f prefix mean int and fp
01867      * RAT for all Renaming logic, random accessible checkpointing is used, but only update when instruction retires.
01868      * FRAT will be read twice and written once per instruction;
01869      * RRAT will be write once per instruction when committing and reads out all when context switch
01870      * checkpointing is implicit
01871      * Renaming logic is duplicated for each different hardware threads
01872      *
01873      * No Dual-RAT is needed in RS-based OOO processors,
01874      * however, RAT needs to do associative search in RAT, when instruction commits and ROB release the entry,
01875      * to make sure all the renamings associated with the ROB to be released are updated at the same time.
01876      * RAM scheme has # ARchi Reg entry with each entry hold phy reg tag,
01877      * CAM scheme has # Phy Reg entry with each entry hold ARchi reg tag,
01878      *
01879      * Both RAM and CAM have same DCL
01880      */
01881     if (!exist) return;
01882     int  tag, data, out_w;
01883 //  interface_ip.wire_is_mat_type = 0;
01884 //  interface_ip.wire_os_mat_type = 0;
01885 //  interface_ip.wt               = Global_30;
01886     clockRate = coredynp.clockRate;
01887     executionTime = coredynp.executionTime;
01888     if (coredynp.core_ty==OOO)
01889     {
01890     //integer pipeline
01891     if (coredynp.scheu_ty==PhysicalRegFile)
01892     {
01893         if (coredynp.rm_ty ==RAMbased)
01894         {     //FRAT with global checkpointing (GCs) please see paper tech report for detailed explaintions
01895             data                             = 33;//int(ceil(coredynp.phy_ireg_width*(1+coredynp.globalCheckpoint)/8.0));
01896 //          data                             = int(ceil(coredynp.phy_ireg_width/8.0));
01897             out_w                            = 1;//int(ceil(coredynp.phy_ireg_width/8.0));
01898             interface_ip.is_cache            = false;
01899             interface_ip.pure_cam            = false;
01900             interface_ip.pure_ram            = true;
01901             interface_ip.line_sz             = data;
01902             interface_ip.cache_sz            = data*XML->sys.core[ithCore].archi_Regs_IRF_size;
01903             interface_ip.assoc               = 1;
01904             interface_ip.nbanks              = 1;
01905             interface_ip.out_w               = out_w*8;
01906             interface_ip.access_mode         = 2;
01907             interface_ip.throughput          = 1.0/clockRate;
01908             interface_ip.latency             = 1.0/clockRate;
01909             interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_energy = 0;
01910             interface_ip.obj_func_dyn_power  = 0;

01915             interface_ip.num_wr_ports    = coredynp.decodeW;

02217             out_w                            = int(ceil (coredynp.arch_ireg_width/8.0));
